## Parsed with column specification:

## read_table2
buoy_raw <- read_table2(buoy_url)
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   `#YY` = col_character(),
##   MM = col_character(),

##   hh = col_character(),

##   WDIR = col_character(),
##   WSPD = col_character(),

##   APD = col_character(),
##   MWD = col_character(),
##   PRES = col_character(),
##   ATMP = col_character(),
##   WTMP = col_character(),
##   DEWP = col_character(),
##   VIS = col_character(),
##   TIDE = col_character()
## )
head(buoy_raw) ## this is what we need!
## # A tibble: 6 x 18
##   `#YY` MM    DD    hh    mm    WDIR  WSPD  GST   WVHT  DPD   APD   MWD  
##   <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr> <chr>
## 1 #yr   mo    dy    hr    mn    degT  m/s   m/s   m     sec   sec   deg  
## 2 2010  01    01    00    00    999   99.0  99.0  99.00 99.00 99.00 999  
## 3 2010  01    01    00    06    999   99.0  99.0  99.00 99.00 99.00 999  
## 4 2010  01    01    00    12    999   99.0  99.0  99.00 99.00 99.00 999  
## 5 2010  01    01    00    18    999   99.0  99.0  99.00 99.00 99.00 999  
## 6 2010  01    01    00    24    999   99.0  99.0  99.00 99.00 99.00 999  
## # ... with 6 more variables: PRES <chr>, ATMP <chr>, WTMP <chr>,
## #   DEWP <chr>, VIS <chr>, TIDE <chr>
buoy <- buoy_raw

## 1. overwrite column names
names(buoy) <- str_c(names(buoy),                  ## current header
                  buoy %>% filter(`#YY` == "#yr"), ## row1 -- don't say buoy[1,] 
                  sep = "_")                       ## separate by `_`

## inspect
names(buoy) ## Looks a lot better
##  [1] "#YY_#yr"   "MM_mo"     "DD_dy"     "hh_hr"     "mm_mn"    
##  [6] "WDIR_degT" "WSPD_m/s"  "GST_m/s"   "WVHT_m"    "DPD_sec"  
## [11] "APD_sec"   "MWD_deg"   "PRES_hPa"  "ATMP_degC" "WTMP_degC"
## [16] "DEWP_degC" "VIS_nmi"   "TIDE_ft"
## 2. clean up a bit more to get rid of the `#`s and the `/`s. 
names(buoy) <- str_replace_all(names(buoy), "#", "")  # replace `#` with nothing 
names(buoy) <- str_replace_all(names(buoy), "/", "_") # replace `/` with `_`

## inspect to make sure it worked
names(buoy)
##  [1] "YY_yr"     "MM_mo"     "DD_dy"     "hh_hr"     "mm_mn"    
##  [6] "WDIR_degT" "WSPD_m_s"  "GST_m_s"   "WVHT_m"    "DPD_sec"  
## [11] "APD_sec"   "MWD_deg"   "PRES_hPa"  "ATMP_degC" "WTMP_degC"
## [16] "DEWP_degC" "VIS_nmi"   "TIDE_ft"
## 3. remove redundant row with units
buoy <- buoy %>%
  filter(YY_yr != "#yr")
# Barplot of water temperature
ggplot(buoy, aes(WTMP_degC)) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))  # how to rotate tick labels

# Clearly 999 is not an actual temperature that was observed.
# 999 is frequently used as a missing value code, so we need to convert this to NA
buoy <- buoy %>%
  mutate(WTMP_degC_test = str_replace_all(WTMP_degC, "999.0", ""))

# Barplot of water temperature
ggplot(buoy, aes(WTMP_degC_test)) +
  geom_bar() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90))  # how to rotate tick labels

Combine the benthic and the buoy datasets

names(buoy)
##  [1] "YY_yr"          "MM_mo"          "DD_dy"          "hh_hr"         
##  [5] "mm_mn"          "WDIR_degT"      "WSPD_m_s"       "GST_m_s"       
##  [9] "WVHT_m"         "DPD_sec"        "APD_sec"        "MWD_deg"       
## [13] "PRES_hPa"       "ATMP_degC"      "WTMP_degC"      "DEWP_degC"     
## [17] "VIS_nmi"        "TIDE_ft"        "WTMP_degC_test"
names(benthic)
## [1] "id_name" "point"   "x"       "y"       "id_date" "date"
# Need a date column in the benthic dataset -- need to unite month, day, year
buoy <- buoy %>%
  unite(date, c(YY_yr, MM_mo, DD_dy), sep = "-")

# join datasets
bb_join <- benthic %>%
  left_join(buoy, by = "date")

## let's select a few columns and inspect:
bb_join %>%
  select(id_name, x, y, date, hh_hr, mm_mn, WTMP_degC) %>%
  head()
## # A tibble: 6 x 7
##   id_name                   x     y date       hh_hr mm_mn WTMP_degC
##   <chr>                 <int> <int> <chr>      <chr> <chr> <chr>    
## 1 Pocillopora meandrina  1773  1000 2010-03-12 00    00    23.2     
## 2 Pocillopora meandrina  1773  1000 2010-03-12 00    06    23.2     
## 3 Pocillopora meandrina  1773  1000 2010-03-12 00    12    23.2     
## 4 Pocillopora meandrina  1773  1000 2010-03-12 00    18    23.2     
## 5 Pocillopora meandrina  1773  1000 2010-03-12 00    24    23.2     
## 6 Pocillopora meandrina  1773  1000 2010-03-12 00    30    23.2
# need to get daily mean temperature from the bouy data, then join with benthic
buoy_daily <- buoy %>%
  mutate(temp_clean = as.numeric(gsub("999.0", NA, WTMP_degC))) %>%   # first need to get rid of 999's
  group_by(date) %>%   # then group by date
  summarise(mean_temp = mean(temp_clean, na.rm=T))  # then get mean temperature

# join datasets
bb_join <- benthic %>%
